    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-02-28T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-02-28T08:00:00-05:00" n="708"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d708">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/75: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-02-28T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 28, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 28—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. From Reber: The Liberian committee will discuss immediate sanitary measures
                    to be taken in Monrovia. The British Government is prepared to dispatch a health
                    officer from Sierra Leone immediately for a temporary detail if (first) adequate
                    authority is granted him by Liberian Government and (secondly) funds are made
                    available to him.</p>
                <p>In view of the delay which would be experienced if funds were requested from the
                    Liberian Government, the chairman is anxious to ascertain prior to more formal
                    discussions whether there is a possibility that $5,000 of loan funds could be
                    released on the definite understanding that such release would not prejudice
                    outstanding questions and intended to secure safety of white population and
                    experts to be sent out.</p>
                <pb facs="0798" n="678" xml:id="pg_678"/>
                <p>I have been asked to transmit this message to the Finance Corporation. Therefore,
                    should the Department approve it is respectfully requested that it be forwarded
                    and that the reply be sent either direct to the chairman or through me.
                    [Reber.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
